  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Raw Diamond Sharp Tongues - Advocacy in Kono District by youth in 2018/2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will strengthen the capacity of 300 youths organized in 30 Local Mines Monitoring Groups (LMMG) in six mining communities in Kono District to actively engaged in monitoring artisanal mining activities; Set up 6 core groups to oversee the work of the LMMGs; trainings of LMMGs and Core groups in monitoring and budget advocacy; establishment of an extractive resource centre in Kono; creating awareness building amongst citizens on mining in rural communities; establish mining school clubs and train pupils on rights and extractive industry issues in 6 schools, write a book on mining to be taught in junior secondary schools.</narrative>
  </description>
